1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Long ago, cars were only for rich people.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:08,500
But on a quiet farm, a curious boy named Henry loved machines.

3
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:12,800
He took clocks apart to learn how they worked.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:16,000
Grown ups saw a mess.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,600
Henry saw a lesson.

6
00:00:18,600 --> 00:00:23,600
Later, Henry dreamed that every family could own a car.

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,600
People doubted him.

8
00:00:26,600 --> 00:00:32,000
His first machines wobbled, broke, and puffed smoke.

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:36,300
But Henry studied, fixed, and tried again.

10
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:40,800
Then came his big idea: the assembly line.

11
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:46,200
Cars became easier to build, and families could travel together.

12
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:51,200
Every big dream begins with one small step.

13
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,160
What will you build?

